<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 28 at 9:47PM MDT  by NWS Glasgow</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of east central
Garfield and southwestern McCone Counties through 1030 PM MDT...
At 947 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 15
miles southeast of Hell Creek Rec Area, or 15 miles northeast of
Jordan, moving east at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Nelson Creek Rec Area, Hell Creek Rec Area, Flowing Wells Rest Area
and Van Norman.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
